Class TableGenerator<T>

java.lang.Object

  • Method Details

    • generateTableHeader

      public void generateTableHeader​(java.util.List<T> objects, javafx.scene.control.TableView<T> tableView)
      This method receives a List of objects of type T and generates through reflection the necessary columns for the TableView. After generating the columns, they are added to the table and each object field will be put in one of the columns.
      Parameters:
      objects - List of objects to populate the TableView
      tableView - TableView to add the objects to

    • reloadTableValues

      public void reloadTableValues​(java.util.List<T> objects, javafx.scene.control.TableView<T> tableView)
      This method receives a list of objects and adds them to the TableView without creating the columns
      Parameters:
      objects - List of objects to be added in the table
      tableView - TableView to add the objects to

    • showSelectedRow

      public T showSelectedRow​(javafx.scene.control.TableView<T> tableView)
      This method gets entry from the table selected by the user and returns it as an object.
      Parameters:
      tableView - TableView to select the entry from
      Returns:
      The object T selected by the user
